column5: Hit the river for a few hours today, tough go with ultra clear water but managed a few fish. Was a roe bite today. They would not touch anything else I drifted by them.  They started on the small side.   They got a little bigger with a few more between small and med.   Then they got bigger, or at least this guy.    Tight lines. RF
Man, I really miss fishing for trout in the rivers. Even the small ones are great little scrappers.Thanks for sharing.
Nicely done RF...Beautiful pieces of chrome there
